    "Body": " About Clearmatics Clearmatics is a B2B fintech startup that designs, develops and operates member-owned and member-governed digital cash settlement systems. Founded in 2015 as a London-based Ethereum R&D company, our mission is to reform market infrastructure by disrupting the common denominator across almost every market: cash settlement in fiat currency. We are committed advocates of Open Source development and are active participants in the Web3 community. We have close ties to Ethereum Foundation and the Company is a founding member of the Ethereum Enterprise Alliance. We are scaling rapidly and looking to hire a DOCUMENT AUTOMATION ENGINEER to help drive the next stage of the company's growth. The document automation engineer will be a member of the Platform team, and work closely with the CEO, Platform Architects, and Product Owners, interfacing with the engineering team. As well as being involved in the product design process, the documentation automation engineer is responsible for supporting Clearmatics' internal platform tooling. This role is based in our Clearmatics London office and will be part of the product team. Responsibilities You will be responsible for the following: We are building distributed systems for some of the world's leading financial institutions. You will be heavily involved in solving challenging and complex problems faced in banking and capital markets, using cutting-edge technology. As the document automation engineer, you will be responsible for: Ownership and continued development of in-house document authoring toolchain written in R Developing and maintaining internal web sites based on R Markdown Creating, maintaining, and monitoring automated pipelines for building sites and documents Controlled vocabulary development and maintenance (SKOS - https://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/) Designing or customising LaTex styles, CSS stylesheets, Pandoc and R Markdown templates Supporting site and document authors to resolve layout & rendering issues Requirements Essential Skills & Experience Good knowledge of LaTeX and Markdown and technical document authoring toolchains Proficient in using Linux command line tools and automating flows with Bash shell scripts Good programming skills in at least one scripting language (ie. Python, Ruby, Perl) Experience with web technologies (HTML/CSS, JavaScript) and static site generators (ie. Shiny) Proficient with Git and leveraging version control for document management and change tracking Desirable Skills & Experience Experience with R programming, R Studio, or development/maintenance of CRAN-R packages Familiarity with Semantic Web technologies and tools: W3C SKOS, OWL, RDF Designing or customising LaTex styles, Pandoc templates, and R Markdown templates Creating diagrams and graphics with TikZ and PGF, Graphviz DOT, MetaPost or Asymptote Experience with Continuous Integration systems, Docker containers, or software packaging Experience with SQL databases or big data technologies (ie. Hadoop, Splunk, Neo4j) What we value at Clearmatics: Collaboration and respect Honesty & Humility Ability to challenge opinions with logic and evidence Willingness to work hard and solve hard problems Passion for distributed technology, cryptography, and their implications for society Continuous improvement and learning. If you'd like to make significant contributions to the blockchain ecosystem and think you are a match, then we'd like to hear from you. Benefits: Central London location in bright, spacious offices. Competitive salary. Flexible working and possibility to work remotely. Relocation assistance. Company pension. Hardware budget to give our developers the best equipment. Professional development - annual individual Learning & Development budget. Monthly Friday company meeting with pizza and beers. \"Show and Tell\" sessions - knowledge sharing across teams. Great kitchen filled with your favourite British specialties. Joining a fast-growing, game-changing, FinTech company. Skills Good programming skills in at least one scripting language (ie. Python, Ruby, Perl) Compensation Competitive Applications for this job are currently closed. ", 
